 4 Novemb 1916 Up at 8 a.m. wash off some grime in a shell hole where about 50 other had done the same . Breakfast have to turn to with the rest of bearer at fatigu work at 2nd F.A. one shell lob peril near dugout last night , chuck dirt on to roof woke me out of a sound sleep with a start . Fatigu work we have to turn to do at 2nd Field Dress Stat . fill sand bag . This is our rest from the trench ! Sleep ill tonight cold windi . Off tucker last 3 day . slight diarrhoea . Our squad goe on duti at 2nd Field at 7 p m . stretcher bear from waggon into oper theatr . all night job . Heavi rain poor unfortun wound stray arriv in pitiabl condit . Big stunt on tonight . 1st Brigad to hop over --- take on advanc posit .
